# Core Workflow

- Always follow this order:
  1. Define design tokens (colors/typography)
  2. Build reusable components
  3. Refine and polish later
  4. Ship
- Do not jump into polish early.
- Do not make random design decisions outside the system.

# UI Reference Handling (Critical)

- When a UI reference (Figma/image) is provided:
  - Match layout and structure accurately (pixel-perfect allowed).
  - Do not redesign or simplify unless explicitly requested.

